HEADWORD: Eversive
<hw>E*ver"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Tending to evert or
overthrow; subversive; with <xex>of</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A maxim <qex>eversive</qex> . . . of all justice and morality.</q>
